            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              <div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Maybe its us reading too much into it, but in the show I get that they aren't making that big of a deal out of who Jon's parents are. In the book it was like a giant shadow hanging over the entire book.</div><br />Yeah, but if Jon is half Targaryen, and he's 1/3 of the triple dragon threat, that ends up being a pretty huge deal in the long run.  But, I don't really recall much of it being discussed in the first few books (by that may be because I hardly remember them at all).  So it's possible that the show will pump it up more in future seasons.  I would hope that they pump up the mystery a bit, since, if it does become a big deal, I'd rather there be some lead up to the reveal, rather than just a: ho-hum, yeah Jon is just one of many bastards, no big deal about his parents, la de da, oh wait, HE'S REALLY A TARGARYEN/STARK HYBRID THAT CAN RIDE A DRAGON WHILE IN THE BODY OF A DIREWOLF!!!!! (insert heavy metal music and pyrotechnics here)<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Does whats his face still have the better claim? Aerys's son and Danaery's brother? Then if THEY croak then it would be Jon?</div><br />I don't think that Dany or Jon have all that great of a claim.  Dany, because she's a chick, and Jon, because he's a bastard.  Aegon has the clear right to the throne, being the trueborn son of the crown prince.  Had Rhaegar not been killed, he would have become king on the death of Aerys, Aegon would have then become crown prince, and ascended to the throne on Rhaegar's death.  Viserys wouldn't have even had a right to the throne, despite being a prince, since Rhaegar managed to sire a trueborn son that lived.<br /><br />Edit: I don't think that Jon even has a shot at the throne according to the rules, even if Aegon and Dany were to both die, unless they legitimized him, when they were king and or queen.  A bastard is a bastard, even if it is between two houses.  No clue who would have the closest claim then.  I would think the Targaryen line would be considered dead at that point, and the hunt would be on for the next closest Baratheon relative.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
