              I can't imagine that he isn't.  Especially considering that in the age where there's no DNA testing.  We just have to go on the word of Varys (shakey) and Jon Connington (stronger) that Aegon is who they claim him to be.  But considering how much time they've spent grooming him, I think it's pretty unlikely that they just picked some look-alike as a baby.  Plus, how would they go about proving that he <span style="font-style: italic">isn't</span> Aegon?  All the other pretender people, we've known to be pretenders, since they were either confirmed dead, or we knew that the real person was somewhere else.  All they'd have are the bones of a long dead infant, with no way of confirming whether used to be Targaryen.

              

              
              
